glish: from the Old French and Middle English personal name <i>Vivian</i>, <i>Vivien</i>, from Latin <i>Vivianus</i> (derivative of <i>vivus</i> ‘living’), the name of a 5th-century Christian martyr. As a personal name its comparative rarity in medieval England gave it a distinctiveness that encouraged its use as a surname. Its pronunciation appears to have caused difficulty and it is found in a large variety of forms, not all of which have survived. Developments include the interchange of initial <i>V</i> and <i>F</i>, the interchange of intervocalic <i>v</i> and <i>th</i>, and the further interchange of <i>th</i> and <i>d</i>; thus <i>Vivian</i> became <i>Fivian</i>, which became <i>Fithian</i>, which became <i>Fidian</i>. See also   Fithen  .","French: mainly southern variant of the personal name <i>Vivien</i> (see 1 above).","Spanish and Galician (<b>Vivián</b>): from the personal name <i>Vivián</i> (see 1 above). Compare   Bibian  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Fithen","meanings":["English and Welsh: variant of   Vivian  . Compare   Fithian  ."]},{"name":"Viviano","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Antonio, Vito, Salvatore, Sal, Angelo, Carlo, Cesare, Gaetano, Gaspare, Geno, Lorenzo.","Italian: from the personal name <i>Viviano</i>, Latin <i>Vivianus</i> (see   Vivian  )."]},{"name":"Vivion","meanings":["Altered form of French   Vivian  .","History: This surname is listed in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors."]}]},{"name":"Ralph","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Norman French name, <i>Raulf</i>, a contracted form of the Germanic personal name <i>Radulf</i>, derived from <i>rād</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Ralf","meanings":["From a Norman French name, <i>Raulf</i>, a contracted form of the Germanic personal name <i>Radulf</i>, derived from <i>rād</i> ‘counsel’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’. The spelling with <i>-ph</i> is due to classical influence in the 18th century."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Ralph Vivian was born about 1175, in Cornwall, England, United Kingdom, his father, Vyvell Vyvian, was 26 and his mother, Anne, was 22. He died in Penzance, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1175–":"umbes 1175–Surnud","1175–Male":"1175–Surnud","1178–Female":"1178–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1204–1268":"1204–1268","1150–1175":"1150–1175","1154–Female":"1154–Surnud","1204":"1204","1268":"1268","1178":"1178","1154":"1154","1175":"1175","1150":"1150","about 1175":"umbes 1175","Trevidren Manor, Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England","Trevidren, Penzance, Cornwall, England":"Penzance, Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1175–":"noin 1175–Kuollut","1175–Male":"1175–Kuollut","1178–Female":"1178–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1204–1268":"1204–1268","1150–1175":"1150–1175","1154–Female":"1154–Kuollut","1204":"1204","1268":"1268","1178":"1178","1154":"1154","1175":"1175","1150":"1150","about 1175":"noin 1175","Trevidren Manor, Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England","Trevidren, Penzance, Cornwall, England":"Penzance, Cornwall, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornwall, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1175–":"environ 1175–Décédé","1175–Male":"1175–Décédé","1178–Female":"1178–Décédée","–Female":"Décédée","1204–1268":"1204–1268","1150–1175":"1150–1175","1154–Female":"1154–Décédée","1204":"1204","1268":"1268","1178":"1178","1154":"1154","1175":"1175","1150":"1150","about 1175":"environ 1175","Trevidren Manor, Cornwall, England":"Cornouailles, Angleterre","Trevidren, Penzance, Cornwall, England":"Penzance, Cornouailles, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornouailles, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque 